The meaning of text[::-1]

This is called slicing in Python.
The general slice syntax is:

sequence[start:stop:step]

Part	Meaning	Example
start	Where to begin	text[1:] â†’ from index 1 onward
stop	Where to stop (exclusive)	text[:4] â†’ up to index 3
step	How much to move each time	text[::2] â†’ every 2nd character
ğŸ” Now, [::-1] means:

Start: not specified â†’ start from the end

Stop: not specified â†’ go all the way to the start

Step: -1 â†’ move backwards (reverse order)

âœ… Example:

text = "Django"
print(text[::-1])


ğŸ§  Process:

Original: D  j  a  n  g  o
Index:    0  1  2  3  4  5


With [::-1] â†’ output becomes "ognajD"

âœ¨ More slice examples
Code	Output	Explanation
text[::1]	Django	normal order
text[::-1]	ognajD	reversed
text[::2]	Dno	every 2nd letter
text[1::2]	jag	start from index 1, every 2nd letter

